<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <!--
    Hardened-runtime entitlements for the notarized Developer ID build. NOT the
    App Sandbox (Daisy is direct-download, not Mac App Store).

    - device.audio-input: required or the hardened runtime silently denies both
      the AVAudioEngine mic capture AND the Core Audio process tap (system audio
      mix). Pairs with NSMicrophoneUsageDescription + NSAudioCaptureUsageDescription
      in Info.plist (the TCC prompt strings).
    - cs.disable-library-validation: Daisy bundles third-party native libraries
      (ONNX Runtime, whisper Metal) that are signed by other teams (or ad-hoc).
      Under the hardened runtime, library validation refuses to load a dylib not
      signed by this app's Team ID, crashing the app at launch. This exception
      permits loading them. Revisit once we confirm which native deps are static
      vs dynamic on macOS — drop this if nothing dynamic remains.
  -->
  <key>com.apple.security.device.audio-input</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
  <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
